article.headline: Norfolk St. 82, Winston-Salem 67
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Michael Deloach scored 23 points on 9-of-12 shooting and Tony Murphy added 14 points to lead Norfolk State to an 82-67 win over Winston-Salem State on Monday. Deloach scored seven points in a 22-3 first-half run for the Spartans (9-9), which led by as many 18 in the opening period. Norfolk led 43-29 at the half and Winston-Salem got no closer than eight points the rest of the way. Rashid Cann and Corey Lyons each added 12 points for the Spartans. Isiah Tucker led the Rams (7-11) with 16 points on 7-of-16 shooting. Jamal Durham added 15 points and four rebounds and Darrell Wonge had 14 points and five rebounds. Norfolk outshot Winston-Salem 52 percent to 39 percent, but was outrebounded by the Rams 39-29.
